--- rfc9442.txt (Section 3.4: SCHC Rules)
+++ rfc9442-migrated.txt (Section 3.4: SCHC Rules)
@@ -358,8 +358,11 @@
 3.4.  SCHC Rules

-   The RuleID MUST be included in the SCHC header.  The total number of
-   Rules to be used directly affects the RuleID field size, and
-   therefore the total size of the fragmentation header.  For this
-   reason, it is RECOMMENDED to keep the number of Rules that are
-   defined for a specific device to the minimum possible.
+   The RuleID MUST be included in the SCHC header of the SCHC Datagram.
+   The RuleID is evaluated within the Context of the selected Instance.
+   The total number of Rules in the Set of Rules (SoR) directly affects
+   the RuleID field size, and therefore the total size of the fragmentation
+   header.  For this reason, it is RECOMMENDED to keep the number of Rules
+   that are defined in the Context for a specific Instance to the minimum
+   possible.

